<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="587" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,150,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Triapitsyn, S. V." box="[341,537,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="587" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref6567" refString="Triapitsyn, S. V. (2010) Revision of the Palaearctic species and review of the Oriental species of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae), with notes on extralimital taxa. Zootaxa, 2381 (1), 1 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2381.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Triapitsyn (2010)</bibRefCitation>
described females of this species as having F1, F2, and F5 slightly longer and F8 slightly shorter; however, the antenna of our female from 
<collectingCountry box="[807,874,258,284]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="587">China</collectingCountry>
has F1–F3 subequal in length and F4–F8 slightly shorter than the preceding funicle segments. We interpret this difference as infraspecific variation. The fore wing disc is also densely setose behind the base of the submarginal vein, but other features are consistent with the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
